{"key":"post-12683589","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12683589</id>\n<content>I've used the same glass lamp for quite a few years.&amp;nbsp; I'm sure yours just got damaged in shipment or had a manufacturing defect.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As for how much alcohol they use, not much.&amp;nbsp; However, they'll evaporate more alcohol out between uses than is consumed during use.&amp;nbsp; Don't fill it more than 1/4 full each time so you don't have much left over.&amp;nbsp; Chances are, it won't still be there the next time you go to use it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I learned the hard way to ALWAYS have a fire extinguisher in the room at all times when using alcohol for sanitizing at the same time a lamp is burning.&amp;nbsp; Keep the lamp and your bottle of alcohol at opposite ends of your work table, and get a dispenser for the alcohol rather than pouring it out of the bottle.&amp;nbsp; Less will spill this way if you accidentally knock it over.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12684578</next>\n<prev>12683433</prev>\n<first>12683339</first>\n<last>12686630</last>\n<when>1275663919</when>\n<utime>06/04/10 06:05 PM</utime>\n</post>"}